Package sprouts

Interface Vars<T extends @Nullable Object>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the properties.
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<T>, Vals<T>
public interface Vars<T extends @Nullable Object> extends Vals<T>
A mutable list of mutable properties designed for MVVM, that can be observed for changes through a Vals.view() by registering Subscriber types on it like Observers and Actions. So you can only observe changes actively by calling Vals.view() and then registering change listeners onto the returned Viewables delegate, which is a weakly referenced state delegate. Take a look at Viewables.onChange(Action) for more information.

If you want to encapsulate the mutability of this type, consider taking a look at the Vals supertype, which you can use for upcasting.
Use Observable.subscribe(Observer) if you want to be notified of changes to the list without any further information about the kind of change itself. Note that a Viewables will be garbage collected alongside all of its change listeners when no longer referenced. So make sure to keep a reference to it around where you are actively listening for changes.

The name of this class is short for "variables". This name was deliberately chosen because it is short, and yet clearly conveys the same meaning as other names used to model this kind of pattern, like "properties", "observable objects", "observable values", "observable properties", etc.

Notice! Instead of this class, we recommend using the Tuple type inside a single Var property declared as Var<Tuple<T>>, as it more compatible with functional and data-oriented programming. This is because the Tuple type is immutable and can be used as part of record based view models, which are more predictable and easier to reason about.

You may also want to take a look at the living sprouts documentation where you can browse a large collection of examples demonstrating how to use the API of this or other classes.
